The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for traffic classification, which involves both feature extraction and classification phases. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with encrypted traffic classification, which could fall under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper involves the use of autoencoders and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper deals with multimedia traffic classification, which could fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
